      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RED HOT TINA (1) is a progressive dog who scored her 3rd career win last time at Gosford, scoring by 3 lengths (22.04). Won at her only start from this draw. Hard to fault her recent form and can win again. BAD KNEES (2) doesn't win out of turn. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when third (29.93) at this track. Goes very well here finding the frame in each of four starts. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Leading player again. ZIPPING PERCAT (6) turned in a good run last time, finishing in the placings (34.83) at this track in a Mix. Lines up from box 6 for the first time. All two career wins have been at this trip. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. Racing well and deserves a win. MRS. MINIVER (4) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
